label.value: skin sodium level

value.value: Quantification of the amount of sodium atoms or ions in a specified sample of skin.

label.value: skin chloride level

value.value: Quantification of the amount of chloride ions, that is, univalent anionic chlorine ions, in a specified sample of skin.

label.value: skin water level

value.value: Quantification of the amount of water in a specified sample of skin.

label.value: calculated skin electrolyte measurement

value.value: A measurement, which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of any electrolyte(s) in skin.

label.value: skin potassium level to skin dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of potassium atoms or ions in a specified sample of skin is divided by the dry weight of that skin sample and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin sodium level to skin dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of sodium atoms or ions in a specified sample of skin is divided by the dry weight of that skin sample and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin chloride level to skin dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of chloride atoms or ions in a specified sample of skin is divided by the dry weight of that skin sample and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin water level to skin dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of water in a specified sample of skin is divided by the dry weight of that skin sample and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin potassium level plus skin sodium level to skin water level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the sum of the amount of potassium in a specified sample of skin and the amount of sodium in that sample of skin is divided by the amount of water in the same sample of skin.

label.value: skin potassium level to skin water level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of potassium in a specified sample of skin is divided by the amount of water in the same sample of skin and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin sodium level to skin water level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of sodium in a specified sample of skin is divided by the amount of water in the same sample of skin and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: skin chloride level to skin water level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of chloride in a specified sample of skin is divided by the amount of water in the same sample of skin and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: blood cystatin level

value.value: The amount of any cystatin (that is, of any member of the cystatin superfamily of proteins, many of which act as cysteine protease inhibitors) found in a specified sample of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them.

label.value: blood cystatin C level

value.value: The amount of the protein cystatin C found in a specified sample of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. Cystatin C is a member of the cystatin superfamily of proteins, is the most abundant extracellular inhibitor of cysteine proteases, and can be found in high concentrations in biological fluids.

label.value: plasma cystatin C level

value.value: The amount of the protein cystatin C found in a specified sample of plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended.

label.value: serum cystatin C level

value.value: The amount of the protein cystatin C found in a specified sample of serum, the clear liquid that separates from blood after it has clotted completely, i.e. blood plasma from which fibrinogen has been removed.

label.value: nose to tail body mass index

value.value: A calculated measurement of body size in which the weight of an animal is divided by the square of the body length, where body length is measured from the tip of the nose to the tip (that is, the distal end) of the tail.

label.value: nose to rump body mass index

value.value: A calculated measurement of body size in which the weight of an animal is divided by the square of the body length, where body length is measured from the tip of the nose to the rump, that is, the base of the tail.

label.value: renal plasma flow to body weight ratio

value.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of plasma that perfuses the kidneys per unit time per amount of body weight.

label.value: glomerular filtration rate to body weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which glomerular filtration rate, an estimate of the volume of fluid filtered from the kidney glomerular capillaries into the Bowman's capsule per specified unit of time, is divided by the total weight of the body and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: kidney sclerotic glomerular volume to total kidney glomerular volume ratio

value.value: A calculated value in which the volume of glomeruli with lesions resulting from fibrosis, scarring or hyaline deposits is divided by the total volume of glomeruli in a specified sample of kidney and presented as a ratio, fraction or quotient, thus normalizing it to the total volume of glomeruli.

label.value: plasma angiotensin II level to plasma angiotensin I level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of angiotensin II in a specified sample of blood plasma is divided by the amount of angiotensin I in the same or a comparable sample of blood plasma, and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: blood hemoglobin A1c level

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of hemoglobin A1c (hemoglobin glycosylated as a result of the nonenzymatic attachment of a glucose/hexose moiety) in a specified sample of blood is divided by the amount of total hemoglobin in that same sample, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: heart left ventricle weight to tibia length ratio

value.value: A calculated value in which the weight of the heart left ventricle is divided by the length of the tibia (the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg of bipeds or hindlimb of quadrupeds which articulates with the femur, fibula, and talus), and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage,thus normalizing it to the length of the leg and, by extension, to the size of the body.

label.value: calculated heart blood flow measurement

value.value: Any measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the movement of blood into, through or out of the heart.

label.value: E/A wave ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the value of the E wave (that is, the velocity of the blood flow across the mitral valve during passive filling of the left ventricle in early diastole) is divided by the value of the A wave (that is, the velocity of the blood flow across the mitral valve during active filling of the left ventricle caused by atrial contraction in late diastole).

label.value: artery tunica media width to artery inner diameter ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the average width of the tunica media is divided by the inner diameter (that is, the diameter of the lumen) of the artery and the result is presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: heart interventricular end-diastolic septal wall  thickness

value.value: The thickness, width or depth of the septal wall of the heart ventricles (that is, the portion of the wall between the left and right ventricles that is shared between the two) at the end of diastole when the heart muscle is maximally relaxed.

label.value: heart interventricular end-systolic septal wall thickness

value.value: The thickness, width or depth of the septal wall of the heart ventricles (that is, the portion of the wall between the left and right ventricles that is shared between the two) at the end of systole when the heart muscle is maximally contracted.

label.value: tissue ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a specified tissue.

label.value: adrenal gland ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNA) of which the tissue of the adrenal gland is formed or composed.

label.value: brain ribonucleic acid level

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the brain is formed or composed.

label.value: lung ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the lung is formed or composed.

label.value: muscle ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which muscle tissue is formed or composed.

label.value: spleen ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the spleen is formed or composed.

label.value: testis ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which testis tissue is formed or composed.

label.value: thymus ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the thymus is formed or composed.

label.value: uterus ribonucleic acid composition measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the uterus is formed or composed.

label.value: body weight to body length (nose to rump) ratio

definition.value: A calculated value in which the total body weight of an organism is divided by the length of the organism from the distance between the tip of the nose to the base of the tail, and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to  the length of the body.

label.value: body weight to body length (nose to tail) ratio

definition.value: A calculated value in which the total body weight of an organism is divided by the length of the organism from the distance between the tip of the nose to the distal end of the tail, and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to  the length of the body.

label.value: body weight area under curve (AUC)

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which a series of body weight measurements is plotted against time for a single individual and the extent of the two dimensional region bounded by the curve and the axes of the graph is determined.

label.value: calculated whole body visceral fat weight

definition.value: Measurement of the whole body visceral fat which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

label.value: whole body visceral fat weight to body length (nose to rump) ratio

definition.value: A calculated value in which the whole body visceral fat weight is divided by the length of the organism from the tip of the nose to the base of the tail, and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the length of the body.

label.value: systolic blood pressure variability

definition.value: A variability measurement in which the mean is calculated from the standard deviations or the standard deviation is calculated from the means of sequential one hour systolic blood pressure measurements.

label.value: diastolic blood pressure variability

definition.value: A variability measurement in which the mean is calculated from the standard deviations or the standard deviation is calculated from the means of sequential one hour diastolic blood pressure measurements.

label.value: mean arterial blood pressure variability

definition.value: A variability measurement in which the mean is calculated from the standard deviations or the standard deviation is calculated from the means of sequential one hour mean arterial blood pressure measurements.

label.value: heart rate variability

value.value: Heart rate variability (HRV) is the physiological phenomenon of variation in the time interval between heartbeats. It is measured by the variation in the beat-to-beat interval.

label.value: horizontal distance covered resulting from voluntary locomotion in proximity to the target  in an experimental apparatus to total horizontal distance covered ratio

definition.value: The ratio of the sum of the horizontal distance of an experimental subject made in proximity to the target to the total horizontal distance made within an apparatus. These movements are the results of voluntary locomotion of the experimental subject.

label.value: calculated horizontal distance resulting from voluntary locomotion in an experimental apparatus
ratio of number of glomeruli with microaneurysms to number of total glomeruli

definition.value: A calculated value in which the number of glomeruli with microaneurysm (focal dilation of arteriocapillary junctions), is divided by the total number of glomeruli in the kidney and presented as a ratio, fraction or quotient, thus normalizing it to the total number of glomeruli.
